The paper deals with the task of land cover mapping using satellite imagery, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) domain. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning models for this task, which suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) domain as well. The paper also discusses the use of weakly supervised learning strategies, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) domain. The paper deals with remote sensing data, which suggests that it could belong to the graphics (cs.GR) domain. Finally, the paper discusses the use of global land cover products, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) domain.
